{"bill": {"@bill-stage": "Introduced-in-Senate", "@public-private": "public", "legis-body": {"#tail": "\n", "section": [{"@section-type": "section-one", "#tail": "\n    ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t", "quote": {"short-title": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Medical Debt Responsibility Act of\n\t\t\t 2013"}, "#tail": ".", "#text": "\n          "}, "#text": "This Act may be cited as\n\t\t\t the ", "@display-inline": "no-display-inline"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "1."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "Short\n\t\t\t title"}, "#text": "\n      ", "@id": "S1"}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "2."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t", "#text": "Findings and\n\t\t\t purpose"}, "subsection": [{"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t finds that\u2014", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Congress", "@entity-id": "0001"}, "#text": "\n          "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(a)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Findings"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "medical debt is\n\t\t\t unique, and Americans do not choose when accidents happen or when illness\n\t\t\t strikes;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(1)"}, "@id": "IDa5b1af4415464a34bdf6f2fbe6df5226", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "medical debt\n\t\t\t collection issues affect both insured and uninsured consumers;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(2)"}, "@id": "IDbcdda14bdaad43bf9fe9e2c2b2d8dd4a", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "according to\n\t\t\t credit evaluators, medical debt collections are more likely to be in dispute,\n\t\t\t inconsistently reported, and of questionable value in predicting future payment\n\t\t\t performance because it is atypical and nonpredictive;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(3)"}, "@id": "ID17a286cb7ff142af98daa5918bf0643a", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "nevertheless,\n\t\t\t medical debt that has been completely paid off or settled can significantly\n\t\t\t damage the credit score of a consumer for years;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(4)"}, "@id": "ID079395c1645240fd8a100708b44d3846", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "as a result,\n\t\t\t consumers may be denied credit or pay higher interest rates when buying a home\n\t\t\t or obtaining a credit card;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(5)"}, "@id": "ID808b59e7734248c4bf558e0998fac038", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "healthcare\n\t\t\t providers are increasingly turning to outside collection agencies to help\n\t\t\t secure payment from patients, coming at the expense of the consumer, because\n\t\t\t medical debts are not typically reported unless they become assigned to\n\t\t\t collections;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(6)"}, "@id": "ID3aea9dbccec54c39b91dfb56cf68c6c9", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "in fact, medical\n\t\t\t bills account for more than half of all non-credit related collection actions\n\t\t\t reported to consumer credit reporting agencies;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(7)"}, "@id": "ID53892422bdd747f390c2a7e3cc975982", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "the issue of\n\t\t\t medical debt affects millions of consumers;"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(8)"}, "@id": "ID1cd46a70c27d45008d15628a5df25090", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "according to the\n\t\t\t Commonwealth Fund, medical bill problems or accrued medical debt affects\n\t\t\t roughly 73,000,000 working-age adults in America; and"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(9)"}, "@id": "ID881337749dee47b7b785a26c4dcfb9fb", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "in 2010,\n\t\t\t 30,000,000 working-age American adults were contacted by a collection agency\n\t\t\t for unpaid medical bills."}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(10)"}, "@id": "IDe070f55a62d44bd2a0b8473334bd457f", "#text": "\n          "}], "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "ID0f144761f4ac48cc9838c0cc58972ed4"}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t", "#text": "It\n\t\t\t is the purpose of this Act to exclude from consumer credit reports medical debt\n\t\t\t that had been characterized as debt in collection for credit reporting purposes\n\t\t\t and has been fully paid or settled."}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(b)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Purpose"}, "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "ID0fdd6cabef05423b9978f754a9f96324"}], "#text": "\n      ", "@id": "IDc81a34519ce846b08420fd0a7333a987"}, {"#tail": "\n  ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "3."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t", "#text": "Amendments to\n\t\t\t fair credit reporting Act"}, "subsection": [{"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "\n          ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity": {"#tail": " is amended by adding at the end the following:", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " (", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "Section 603 of the Fair Credit Reporting Act", "@value": "Fair Credit Reporting Act/s:603"}, {"#tail": ")", "@entity-type": "uscode", "#text": "15 U.S.C.\n\t\t\t 1681a", "@value": "usc/15/1681a"}], "@entity-type": "law-citation", "#text": "\n            "}}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(a)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Medical debt\n\t\t\t defined"}, "quoted-block": 